<br />
Always resisted... Since when? <br />
<br />
Are you using SoS on fire resistant mobs? White fire on magic resistant mobs? <br />
<br />
There are, of course, instances where we have to use a different (and yes, sometimes smaller) nuke. But this isn't a constant thing. Resists are actually a pretty good attempt at balance. Does a melee successfully hit with every attempt? No. Do we successfully do 2740 damage on every SoS? No. <br />
<br />
Yes, I can understand when you're doing GoD trials and some mobs just don't take nukes, but that's when you switch. And you switch. And you figure out what spells to use when. Don't use SoS or WF all the time. Hell, we've got lures. They're good for those bosses in Qvic! Use them there! So for a couple mobs you can't do 8k crits. Deal with it.</div>
